column5: Long road trip for a day of birds with my brother. Didn't see anyone else the whole day. My brother got 3 and I never pulled the trigger. That's grouse hunting.  Spruce grouse hen in his right hand.   Me just walkin' through the woods.     Last bird of the day while I was trying my luck off-trail.  That's the smirk of a little brother who has 3 birds to zero and got the last one whilst I was slugging through the think stuff.
Thats some nice eat,n there Rob. As for the zero, I,ll bet you felt good after that bush walk. I always think about the good work out I get when trashing through the bush.
Looks like an ideal day to be walking the woods, love the light dusting of snow. Your brother looks quite pleased.
Ah nice work!  Had bacon wrapped grouse chunks last night at a birthday party, MMMMmmmmm.
